physical_appearance: This is a photograph of the Sule Pagoda in Rangoon, Burma. The pagoda, with its towering stupa, is on the left of the photograph. On the right, there is a two-tiered wooden structure with open archways, with a three-step base. The structure is on an open plot of grass. The title is written at the bottom, below the photograph.
title_text: Photograph album of views and portraits in the Punjab, Cashmere, Ceylon, Burma, Penang, Singapore, and Java Sule Pagoda and Band stand, Rangoon
